Maros Sefcovic is reportedly set to announce new concessions but has threatened a trade war if the UK refuses to agree a compromise. The Telegraph reported that Mr Sefcovic was willing to agree significant compromises to virtually eliminate all customs and food safety checks between Britain and Northern Ireland, similar to the deal struck with regard to medicines. The apparent olive branch comes despite Brussels also threatening a trade war, should the UK push ahead with the new legislation. In a statement on Tuesday, the EU said: “Should the UK decide to move ahead with a bill disapplying constitutive elements of the Protocol as announced today by the UK Government, the EU will need to respond with all measures at its disposal.” FOLLOW BELOW FOR LIVE UPDATES...